What is the structure of your dataset?¶

There are 519700 individual rides made in a bike-sharing system in the dataset with 7 features

  • Trip Duration (seconds)
  • Start Time and Date
  • End Time and Date
  • Start Station Name
  • End Station Name
  • Bike ID
  • User Type (Subscriber or Customer Subscriber = Member or Customer = Casual)

What is/are the main feature(s) of interest in your dataset?¶

I am more interested in finding out which are the stations with the most trips in SF and when trips are taken in terms of time, how long they take, and does it depend on if a user is a subscriber or customer.

What features in the dataset do you think will help support your investigation into your feature(s) of interest?¶

  • Trip Duration (seconds)
  • Start Station Name
  • End Station Name
  • Start Time and Date
  • End Time and Date
  • User Type

In [11]:
# To simplify time analysis (extract months in separate column)
df['start_time_bymonth'] = df['start_time'].dt.month
df['end_time_bymonth'] = df['end_time'].dt.month
In [12]:
sb.countplot(data=df,x='start_time_bymonth')
plt.title('number of trips in per month');
plt.gcf().set_size_inches(10, 6);

We can see the October ,September and November are the most months to trips in SF, followed by August and December, And June as the lowest.

Multivariate Exploration¶

Create plots of three or more variables to investigate the data even further.

In [18]:
plt.gcf().set_size_inches(17, 9)
markers = [['Customer', 'o'],['Subscriber', '^']]
for cat, marker in markers:
    df_cat = df[df['user_type'] == cat]
    plt.scatter(data = df_cat, x = 'start_time_bymonth', y = 'duration_mins', marker = marker , alpha = 1/8)
plt.legend(['Customer','Subscriber'])
plt.title('Trip duration based months Against User type')
plt.xlabel('Start Time By Months')
plt.ylabel('Duration By Mins');
In [19]:
#to more Accuracy and assurance
g = sb.FacetGrid(data = df, col = 'user_type', col_wrap = 2, height = 8)
g.map(plt.scatter, 'start_time_bymonth', 'duration_mins', alpha= 1/8)
plt.xlabel('Start Time By Months')
plt.ylabel('Duration By Mins');

From the charts above we can infer that most long trips come from the customer.

It is normal for customer to be the most inclined to long trips, but it is surprising that we found that there are also some subscribers who tend to trips exceeding 400 minutes most of the months.
